-- Finance Ministry Sells Seven-Year China Bonds at 2.76% Yield, Trader Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-21T02:35:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/finance-ministry-sells-seven-year-china-bonds-at-2-76-yield-trader-says.html

          
          
             China’s finance ministry sold 28
billion yuan ($4.1 billion) in seven-year bonds at an average
yield of 2.76 percent, according to traders at Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China Ltd. and Bank of China Ltd.  
 The highest winning-bid yield at the sale was 2.81 percent,
said the traders at the primary dealers required to bid at the
government auctions.  
 The average yield at today’s auction was 1 basis point
higher than the 2.75 percent median estimate in a Bloomberg News
survey of 18 finance companies. A basis point is 0.01 percentage
point.  
